                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "Bashify pivots across internal Linux and Unix hosts using SSH with credentials or keys recovered from compromised systems. SSH-based lateral movement allows the actor to traverse server infrastructure and reach sensitive internal systems — including mail servers and data repositories — without deploying additional implants beyond standard SSH tooling."
