                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "Bashify uses Telegram bots as a command-and-control channel, routing operational commands and collected data through the platform's application-layer protocol API. Telegram's use of legitimate HTTPS endpoints makes C2 traffic indistinguishable from normal messaging activity on network monitoring systems, and the platform provides the actor with a resilient, low-infrastructure C2 option that is difficult to block without impacting legitimate business use."
                ],
