        {
            "id": "malware",
            "instance": "1cadb272-1df6-4ef9-bf2b-daf82d4915ab",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "Mail Protocol C2 (T1071.003)"
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "In The Matrix uses mail protocols — such as SMTP, IMAP, or POP3 — as an alternative command-and-control channel, blending C2 traffic with legitimate email traffic flows. Mail protocol C2 is particularly effective in environments where web-based C2 channels are monitored, as email protocol traffic is often permitted outbound with less scrutiny than arbitrary HTTPS connections."
                ],
                [
